==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Out-of-door
<hw>Out`-of-door"</hw>, <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being out of
the house; being, or done, in the open air; suited for the open air;
outdoor; <as>as, <ex>out-of-door</ex> exercise</as>. See <cref>Out of
door</cref>, under <er>Out</er>, <pos>adv.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Amongst <qex>out-of-door</qex> delights.</q> <rj><qau>G.
Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>out-of-doors</ent>⟦br⟧
